+# UI/UX Audit & Redesign Recommendations
+
+## 1. Executive Summary
+
+The site has a useful foundation: static HTML, fast CDN Leaflet maps, a searchable directory, and a separate analytical report/gap scanner. The biggest issue is trust. Public copy and hard-coded metrics still describe the old 450-record dataset while the current static data contains 754 businesses, 481 coordinate-bearing map features, 457 Google Maps CIDs, 521 phones, 361 Instagram handles, and 328 Facebook URLs. A visitor cannot tell which page is current.
+
+The second major issue is information architecture. The landing page is only a link list, while the directory and gap map contain the real value. The first screen should communicate the project status, show the spatial coverage, and route users by task: browse businesses, inspect coverage gaps, read methodology, or download data.
+
+The third issue is maintainability. `report.html` embeds an old GeoJSON snapshot and old report tables directly in the page, while `directory.html` and `gapmap.html` fetch `businesses.json`. This guarantees drift. The redesign should use one data source for counts and client-rendered summary widgets across pages.
+
+## 2. Per-Page Audit
+
+### Landing: `index.html`
+
+What works:
+
+- It loads instantly and has clear links to the three major artifacts.
+- The page is simple enough for GitHub Pages and has no build dependency.
+
+What does not work:
+
+- The headline/subtitle still says 450 businesses and 99.8% Instagram coverage. Current data is 754 businesses and 361 Instagram handles, about 47.9% coverage if calculated against all records.
+- It does not explain the difference between total records and mapped records. The right public message is: 754 total records, 481 mapped with coordinates.
+- There is no map or visual evidence of the 5 km scope, so the geographic premise is abstract.
+- The links are plain cards with weak hierarchy. "Browse Directory" should be the primary CTA; "Download CSV" and "GitHub" should be secondary utilities.
+- There is no visible data version/date, source summary, or evidence summary.
+
+Concrete fixes:
+
+- Replace the subtitle with dynamic stats loaded from `businesses.json`.
+- Add a compact landing map using `businesses.geojson` or coordinate records from `businesses.json`.
+- Add four high-signal stats: `754 records`, `481 mapped`, `361 Instagram`, `521 phones`.
+- Add a source/evidence strip: PVS crawl, OSM, Google Maps grid scan, SQLite cache, Playwright Instagram verification, 255 screenshots.
+- Add persistent top navigation shared with the other pages.
+
+### Directory: `directory.html`
+
+What works:
+
+- Search, area filter, Instagram filter, and category pills make the dataset usable.
+- Cards are readable and expose contact/social fields directly.
+- The map can sync from a selected business card.
+- Fetching `businesses.json` keeps the page closer to the live dataset than `report.html`.
